description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FORTUNESWELL PHARMACY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based at Dorset County Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Haematology and Oncology Outpatients Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dispensing Assistant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting new opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and highly motivated individual to join our new Fortuneswell Pharmacy team as a Dispensing Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortuneswell Pharmacy is a wholly owned subsidiary Outpatient Pharmacy located in the Fortuneswell Chemotherapy Unit at Dorset County Hospital. Our service includes the supply of medicines and pharmaceutical advice to haematology and oncology outpatients. We are a people centered business, where every member of staff matters and can make a difference. Patients are at the heart of everything we do. Joining Fortuneswell Pharmacy means becoming part of a team of dedicated staff who are committed to leading the way through clinical excellence and great customer care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and self-motivated individual interested in developing skills within hospital outpatient pharmacy services. Working alongside the Superintendent Pharmacist and Specialist Haematology and Oncology colleagues you will be actively involved in the exciting development of patient services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will involve duties that assist the pharmacist in the dispensing process to provide a safe an efficient service to haematology and oncology patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have a good general education and demonstrable computer experience. You will be systematic and have a good eye for detail and accuracy. If not already held, you will take part in the NVQ Level 2 in Pharmacy Services, or an equivalent qualification (in house training will be provided).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prior pharmacy experience is desirable, but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary negotiable dependent upon experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrew Harris, Superintendent Pharmacist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortuneswell Pharmacy 01305 254862 or email: pharmacy@dchsubco.co.uk&lt;/p&gt;
